sql: SELECT T1.name, COUNT(DISTINCT T2.name) FROM buildings AS T1 JOIN Office_locations AS T3 ON T1.id = T3.building_id JOIN Companies AS T2 ON T2.id = T3.company_id WHERE T1.Height >= 100 ORDER BY T1.name ASC
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.name), T2.name FROM buildings AS T1 JOIN Office_locations AS T3 ON T1.id = T3.building_id JOIN Companies AS T2 ON T3.company_id = T2.id WHERE T1.Height < 100
SELECT COUNT(Height) FROM buildings WHERE Status != 'completed'
SELECT T1.name, COUNT(T2.company_id) FROM buildings AS T1 JOIN Office_locations AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.building_id WHERE T1.City != 'New York'
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.name), COUNT(DISTINCT T1.City) FROM buildings AS T1 JOIN Office_locations AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.building_id WHERE T1.Status != 'Abandoned' ORDER BY T1.id DESC LIMIT 10
SELECT MIN(Height) FROM buildings WHERE Height < 100 ORDER BY Height DESC LIMIT 5

SELECT b.name, AVG(o.move_in_year) FROM buildings AS b JOIN Office_locations AS o ON b.id = o.building_id WHERE o.company_id = 1 OR b.City = 'New York' OR EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM Companies AS c WHERE c.id = o.company_id AND c.Sales_billion > 10)

SELECT T1.name, T2.Sales_billion FROM buildings AS T1 JOIN Office_locations AS T3 ON T1.id = T3.building_id JOIN Companies AS T2 ON T3.company_id = T2.id WHERE T2.Sales_billion >= 10 ORDER BY T2.Sales_billion DESC LIMIT 10
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.name) FROM buildings AS T1 WHERE T1.Height > 100 AND T1.Stories > 20 OR EXISTS (SELECT T2.building_id FROM Office_locations AS T2 WHERE T2.building_id = T1.id)
SELECT T1.name FROM buildings AS T1 WHERE T1.Height > ( SELECT AVG(T2.Height) FROM buildings AS T2 ) LIMIT 1
SELECT T1.name FROM Companies AS T1 WHERE T1.name = 'CompanyA'

SELECT T1.name, COUNT(DISTINCT T2.company_id) FROM buildings AS T1 JOIN Office_locations AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.building_id WHERE EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM Companies AS T3 WHERE T3.id = T2.company_id AND T3.Sales_billion > 10)
SELECT AVG(Height) FROM buildings WHERE City > 'New York'
SELECT T1.name FROM buildings AS T1 WHERE T1.Stories > 50
SELECT T1.name FROM buildings AS T1 WHERE T1.City = 'New York' AND T1.Height > 100 AND T1.id NOT IN (SELECT T2.building_id FROM Office_locations AS T2) ORDER BY T1.name DESC

SELECT T1.name FROM buildings AS T1 JOIN Office_locations AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.building_id WHERE T1.name NOT IN (SELECT T3.name FROM Companies AS T3 JOIN Office_locations AS T4 ON T3.id = T4.company_id)
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.name), COUNT(T1.id) FROM buildings AS T1 JOIN Office_locations AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.building_id
